div.p:
Edited from the original by J. F. Fleet () without translation, with estampages of the plates. Fleet's edition and introduction was reproduced in 174-176. Subsequently noticed in 37A/1956-195786 and again in 49A/1962-196317, both without discussion. The text of the Telugu section (without indication of editorial intervention) was published with a translation by Korada Mahadeva Sastri (299-301). The present edition by Dániel Balogh is based on a collation of Fleet's text with his facsimiles and with inked impressions from Sir Walter Elliot's collection.Scans of these impressions were obtained by Emmanuel Francis from the Edinburgh University Library, the Bibliothèque nationale de France and the British Museum. Several re-editions and discussions have yet to be listed here and consulted to improve my edition. 
Additional, untraced bibliography: 
Journal of the Punjab Historical Society, Vol. 5, pp. 174ff (probably 1912-13); 
Bhāratī vol. 2, pp. 286-301 and 661-665 (probably 1925, discussion by M. Somasekhara Sarma);
Bhāratī vol. 5 pt. 2, pp. 96-110 (probably 1928, text and notes by V. Prabhakara Sastry);
Text and notes by M. Somasekhara Sarma: RPS, pp. 71-72 (publication not identified);
Andhra Sahithya Parishat Patrika 22, pp. 174-176 (probably 1933, text and notes by Lakshmana Rao);
Notes by K. V. Lakshmana Rao: Andhra Pariśōdhakamaṇḍali Pancama vārṣikōtsava (no further publication info);
C. Narayana Rao, History of Telugu Language (Andhra-bhasha-charitramu), vol. 1, pp. 1310-1316 (probably 1937, text and notes);
Bhāratī vol. 14, pp. 825-847 (probably 1937, discussion by K. Suryanarayana);
